      "content": "# input types should reflect user intent with simple specific fields\n\nOperation input types should be designed around user intent:\n\n```graphql\n// ✅ Simple, specific — reflects what the user provides\ninput AddLineItemInput {\n    id: OID!\n    description: String!\n    quantity: Int!\n    unitPrice: Amount_Money!\n}\n\n// ❌ Complex nested structure — harder to use and validate\ninput AddLineItemInput {\n    item: LineItemInput!\n    metadata: MetadataInput\n    options: OptionsInput\n}\n```\n\nKeep inputs flat and focused. The system auto-generates `OID` for new objects — callers provide IDs through the input schema because [[reducer purity requires all dynamic values from action input]].\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[schema design]]",
